<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Intake, Inlet, and Exhaust
        Manifolds - Removal - Intake Manifold, Fuel Valve, and Fuel Rail Plugs
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Intake Manifold, Fuel Valve, and Fuel Rail Plugs</title>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0604" count="1">Remove the
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_129.xml" xrefid="s0508">intake side EGR cooler and bracket</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0508"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_170.xml" xrefid="s0707">fuel filter header assembly</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0707"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_79.xml" xrefid="s0315">(IAH) relay assembly</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0315"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350006169" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK14/K14011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake manifold</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 Fuel rail plug (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel valve assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 35 bolt (7)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 35 stud bolt (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, do not smoke and keep fuel away from flames and sparks.
                </para>
            </warning>
            <note>
                <para>Removal of the rear engine lifting eye may be required to access the rear fuel rail plug with the
                    intake manifold on engine.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M12 fuel rail plugs and drain fuel into a correct container marked DIESEL FUEL.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove seven M10 x 35 bolts and four M10 x 35 stud bolts securing the intake manifold to the
                cylinder head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the intake manifold and gasket from the engine. Drain remaining fuel from the intake
                manifold and discard the intake manifold gasket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard O-rings from fuel rail plugs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, remove the fuel valve assembly (air bleed and pressure test port) and discard
                O-ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
